<dl id="n05036e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05036e">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05036e"> 36(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> set out on his way / to repress heresy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When St. Martin went forth from the monastery, and mounted his ass to go and repress heresies, distribute alms to the poor, or overthrow the idols that were still worshipped in many places, the child followed him on foot and waited on him. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 88</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
